A Spanish butcher who cut up his own brother and stored the parts in his fridge-freezer next to his food has been caught after he turned himself in to the police.

Aurele Almanza, 48, claims to have killed his brother Osmas, 52, in self-defence, before slicing the body into pieces, neatly packing them away in freezer bags to escape arrest.

Mr Almanza's crime went undetected for a whole year before he confessed to local police on the Balearic Island of Mallorca.

